          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The deuterium target consisted of  a  vertical  mylar",
                " cylinder (40 mm diameter, 0.08 mm wall thickness)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Input data were the  measured  photon  spectrum,  the",
                " complete  geometry  of  the  apparatus,  and a trial",
                " photodisintegration cross section which was iterated",
                " until the spectra simulated using a MonteCcarlo code",
                " D0180 became compatible,  within statistical errors,",
                " with the measured ones."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 2h(g,p)n    cross    section     was     measured",
                " simultaneously  at  theta-p-cm  =  0,  90,  and  180",
                " degree.  The photon energy range was 98 - 243 MeV. A",
                " quasimonochromatic  photon  beam  was  used  and the",
                " photon  spectrum  measured  on  line   by   a   pair",
                " spectrometer. The results are in good agreement with",
                " the existing measurements of the 0-  and  180-degree",
                " cross sections and confirm the consistency among all",
                " experimental data from monochromatic  photon  beams.",
                " At all measured energies, angular distributions were",
                " extracted and compared with theory.  The data  agree",
                " moderately   well  with  recent  calculations  which",
                " include relativistic effects."
              ]
            }
          ],
